Usage: [options] file/dir
	 FoLiA-idf will produce IDF statistics for a directory of FoLiA files 
	--clip	 clipping factor. 
			 (entries with frequency <= this factor will be ignored). 
	--lower	 Lowercase all words
	--class='name', use 'name' as the folia class for <t> nodes. (default is 'current')
	--strings	 search for String nodes (default is Word)
	-t	 number of threads
	-h or --help	 this message 
	-V or --version	 show version 
	-e	 expr: specify the expression all files should match with.
	-O	 output prefix
	-R	 search the dirs recursively (when appropriate).
